	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><br /><strong>Utility</strong></p><ul><li><p>You summon a storm cloud that forms a massive cylinder: 360 ft. radius, 5,000 ft. high, centered on a point within sight.</p></li><li><p>The storm produces different effects each round, as detailed below. Creatures under the storm are affected once per round unless noted otherwise.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Round Effects</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Round 1:</strong> Each creature under the storm makes a <strong>[[/save CON]]{Constitution Save}</strong>.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Targets takes [[/damage 2d6 thunder]] damage and is &amp;reference[Deafened] for 1 minute.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage and no effect.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Round 2:</strong> Acidic rain pours down. Each creature under the storm takes [[/damage 1d6 acid]].</p></li><li><p><strong>Round 3:</strong> Each creature under the storm makes a <strong>[[/save DEX]]{Dexterity Save}</strong>.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 2d6 lightning]] damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> No damage.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Round 4:</strong> Hailstones rain down. Each creature under the storm takes [[/damage 2d6 bludgeoning]] damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Round 5â€“10:</strong> Heavy rain and strong winds persist. The area is &amp;reference[Heavily Obscured], and rain extinguishes open flames. Ranged weapon attacks are made with Disadvantage, and ground in the area is &amp;reference[Difficult Terrain].</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
